2a:["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-4","children":[["$","div","faq-0",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"How much revenue do heating engineers lose from missed calls?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The average heating engineer misses 4-6 calls daily, with 67% occurring after hours. With callouts at £120-£200 and replacements at £2,500-£4,500, missing 3 calls per week costs £360-£1,000 in callout fees alone, plus replacement sales and service contracts."}]]}],["$","div","faq-1",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"Can AI safely handle gas leak emergency calls?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Yes. The AI identifies gas leak reports, immediately advises calling the National Gas Emergency Service on 0800 111 999, and provides safety instructions (open windows, turn off gas at meter, no flames). It captures the address and contact details for your immediate follow-up after the emergency service attends."}]]}],["$","div","faq-2",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"How does AI distinguish between emergency and routine heating calls?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The AI asks diagnostic questions about vulnerable residents, gas smells, error codes, and water leaks. It classifies genuine emergencies (complete heating failure with vulnerable people, gas leaks, carbon monoxide) as priority. Routine calls (annual services, thermostat issues) get standard scheduling."}]]}],["$","div","faq-3",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"What's the ROI of after-hours call answering for heating engineers?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"At £59/month, one emergency callout (£120-£200) pays for 2-3 months. Most heating engineers capture 3-5 additional jobs weekly in winter. Including replacement sales, ROI exceeds 2,000% during peak season. Landlord contracts captured after-hours provide recurring annual revenue."}]]}],["$","div","faq-4",{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3","children":"How can heating engineers get more landlord contracts?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Landlords call evenings and weekends about gas safety certificates and tenant complaints. AI captures these calls, identifies landlord status, and records property counts and tenant details. Follow up with batch pricing for multiple properties and annual service reminders to build recurring revenue."}]]}]]}]]}]
